                                    <m:msub>
                                        <m:mi mathvariant="normal">μ</m:mi>
                                        <m:mn>0</m:mn>
                                    </m:msub>
                                </m:mrow>
                            </m:math>. The default is "greater."</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Copy this function to R as a single block:</p>
                <code>z.test = function(x, sigma, mu0, alt="greater")</code>
                <code>{</code>
                <code>mu = mean(x);</code>
                <code>n = length(x);</code>
                <code>z = (mu-mu0)/(sigma/sqrt(n))</code>
                <code>if (alt=="less"){p = pnorm(z)}</code>
                <code>else </code>
                <code>{</code>
                <code>if (alt=="two.sided"){p = 2*(1-pnorm(abs(z)))}</code>
                <code>else {p = 1-pnorm(z)}</code>
                <code>}</code>
                <code>paste("mean = ",mu,"n = ",n,", z = ",z,", p-value = ",p)</code>
                <code>}</code>
                <p>To use the function "z.test" on the data already entered, execute the
                    command:</p>
                <code>z.test(epa$COMB.MPG, 4.7, 20, "greater")</code>
                <p>The function <code>z.test</code> returns the sample mean, the sample size, the
                    z-score for the sample and the p-value for the hypothesis test.</p>
