                        <li>Perform: select Hypothesis test for μ </li>
                        <li>Enter a null value for the population mean and choose the form of the
                            alternative hypothesis from the options not equal, less than, and
                            greater than </li>
                        <li>Press Compute! </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>If summaries are given </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Choose: Stat → Z stats → One Sample → With summary </li>
                        <li> Enter Sample mean, standard deviation and sample size.</li>
                        <li>Perform: select Hypothesis test for μ </li>
                        <li>Select Hypothesis Test</li>
                        <li>Enter a null value for the population mean and choose the form of the
                            alternative hypothesis from the options not equal, less than, and
                            greater than </li>
                        <li>Press Compute! </li>
                    </ul>
